  <sec sec-type="results" id="sec011">
    <title>Results</title>
    <p>In this section we conduct different experiments to analyze our newly introduced statistics and resolution function. First, we use the previously defined resolution function and the NNI metric to compare our suggested statistic with the classical ones, and show that the this new statistic exhibit a better performance. We then use our new proposed resolution function to evaluate different tree shape statistics, showing that this new resolution function can classify good and bad statistics. The advantage of this resolution over the previously used one is that its computation reduces the time and space complexity. Lastly, we discuss the optimal pairwise combinations of several other statistics. The following subsections explain each experiment in more detail.</p>
    <sec id="sec012">
      <title>Comparing the power of our suggested statistics with the classical statistics</title>
